theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  -- First inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
    have hIntSub : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono hIntSub
  -- Second inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have hA_sub : A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    -- `A` is an open subset of `closure A`, hence contained in its interior.
    exact interior_maximal (subset_closure : A ⊆ closure A) hA
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have h := closure_mono hA_sub
    simpa [closure_closure] using h
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂
